00:34:02,142 --> 00:34:04,559
I can confirm
that Alan Beck is in custody,

497
00:34:04,729 --> 00:34:07,720
though I cannot elaborate
on the details of his arrest pending

498
00:34:07,903 --> 00:34:11,704
a full investigation. What I can
tell you is that our hostage negotiator,

499
00:34:11,874 --> 00:34:15,990
Captain Horst Cali, along with
Pittsburgh P.D. and our SWAT team,

500
00:34:16,159 --> 00:34:20,143
are in full command of the situation,
and focused on the task at hand.

501
00:34:21,128 --> 00:34:22,493
Getting the hostages

502
00:34:22,653 --> 00:34:26,204
<i>out of harm's way remains our priority.</i>
<i>I won't take questions at this time.</i>

503
00:34:26,835 --> 00:34:29,699
<i>You'll all be briefed again
at the appropriate moment.</i>

504
00:34:33,461 --> 00:34:35,986
<i>We've also just received word
that Cassandra Conforth,</i>

505
00:34:36,136 --> 00:34:40,422
<i>who was shot earlier in the bank, is out
of surgery and is in stable condition</i>

506
00:34:40,573 --> 00:34:42,373
<i>- at this hour.</i>
- Mikey, you hear that?

507
00:34:43,595 --> 00:34:46,772
Mike, you hear that, little brother?
She's gonna be okay, man.

508
00:34:48,279 --> 00:34:50,936
Yeah, but we're not okay, Sarge.
None of us are okay.

509
00:34:52,405 --> 00:34:54,336
And we'll never be okay again.

510
00:35:00,868 --> 00:35:03,147
Okay, everybody, let's hit your posts.
Come on.

511
00:35:03,609 --> 00:35:06,312
Hold on.
What do we do now, Sarge?

512
00:35:06,504 --> 00:35:09,439
- I don't know, we just wait.
- What do you mean you don't know?

513
00:35:39,971 --> 00:35:40,971
What was that?

514
00:35:41,238 --> 00:35:42,463
I don't know.

515
00:35:43,251 --> 00:35:45,759
But it's getting dangerous now, baby.

516
00:35:46,127 --> 00:35:48,924
- We gotta get out of here.
- There's no way out.

517
00:35:49,387 --> 00:35:51,835
Maybe it's nothing.
Maybe there was no banging, you know.

518
00:35:51,957 --> 00:35:53,709
Maybe we were hallucinating.

519
00:35:54,347 --> 00:35:55,464
Explain that, baby?

520
00:35:55,659 --> 00:35:58,313
Not...
Not hallucinating, but maybe, like...

521
00:35:59,452 --> 00:36:00,460
audi-u-nating.

522
00:36:02,363 --> 00:36:04,887
We don't have any food or water.
What are we gonna do?

523
00:36:11,486 --> 00:36:12,803
What is that, water?

524
00:36:13,483 --> 00:36:14,564
I don't know.

525
00:36:16,903 --> 00:36:20,218
- No, don't do it, I'm scared.
- I'll protect you. I promise.

526
00:36:37,956 --> 00:36:40,094
They were like brothers to me, Con...

527
00:36:41,319 --> 00:36:43,608
They were like the brothers I never had.

528
00:36:47,481 --> 00:36:50,326
This mean I'm going home now?
Are you taking me off?

529
00:36:51,317 --> 00:36:52,317
Hell no.

530
00:36:53,990 --> 00:36:55,224
I need you, kid.

531
00:36:56,377 --> 00:36:58,435
I need all the good cops I can get.

532
00:37:11,471 --> 00:37:12,498
How's he doing?

533
00:37:12,705 --> 00:37:14,796
He's all right.
You calling Wolf?

534
00:37:15,222 --> 00:37:17,829
No, I'm gonna let him
stew in his defeat.

535
00:37:18,784 --> 00:37:21,455
- He'll realize he's out of moves.
- You heard about Cass?

536
00:37:22,284 --> 00:37:24,498
- No.
- She's gonna make it, Cap.

537
00:37:24,972 --> 00:37:26,363
Your watch is clean.

538
00:37:30,942 --> 00:37:31,942
Thank you.

539
00:37:36,567 --> 00:37:40,448
I'm on my way to go deal with this
Beck debacle. Should take some time.

540
00:37:41,737 --> 00:37:43,618
I know how much you're gonna miss me.

541
00:37:43,738 --> 00:37:45,141
- Oh, yeah.
- Just remember,

542
00:37:46,102 --> 00:37:47,487
I'm not really gone.

543
00:37:48,250 --> 00:37:49,359
I'll speak to you.

544
00:37:49,889 --> 00:37:51,038
Okay, Chief.

545
00:38:18,466 --> 00:38:20,553
How can you look at me like that?

546
00:38:22,489 --> 00:38:23,872
How can you do that?

547
00:38:25,059 --> 00:38:27,301
After everything I've done to everybody.

548
00:38:28,393 --> 00:38:31,266
Everybody else sees me
for what I really am, except you... Why?

549
00:38:33,269 --> 00:38:34,269
I watch you...

550
00:38:35,938 --> 00:38:38,339
I see the way you are with us,
with that boy.

551
00:38:39,696 --> 00:38:40,996
I hear it in your voice

552
00:38:41,288 --> 00:38:43,480
when you come over here, when we talk.

553
00:38:45,770 --> 00:38:47,924
Maybe I just see
a different side of you.

554
00:39:02,427 --> 00:39:04,675
I'm really sorry
about what happened to your friend.

555
00:39:06,965 --> 00:39:09,988
I wish that would have never happened.
I wish...

556
00:39:10,968 --> 00:39:12,889
I wish a lot of things never happened.

557
00:39:17,395 --> 00:39:19,395
I'm just glad she's gonna be okay.

558
00:39:29,557 --> 00:39:31,732
I didn't mean to yell at you earlier.

559
00:39:32,365 --> 00:39:34,021
I was...
I was just upset.

560
00:39:57,765 --> 00:39:59,686
Why do you keep coming in here for?

561
00:40:00,534 --> 00:40:01,787
Close the door.

562
00:40:07,730 --> 00:40:09,510
I dug a hole to the ladies' room.

563
00:40:16,304 --> 00:40:17,539
What...
What is that?

564
00:40:18,180 --> 00:40:19,532
What do you have there?

565
00:40:24,350 --> 00:40:28,344
This is a life source, brother.

566
00:40:29,512 --> 00:40:31,113
Republican guard.

567
00:40:32,194 --> 00:40:33,841
Fifth Baghdad mech division.

568
00:40:36,615 --> 00:40:37,623
I did...

569
00:40:38,075 --> 00:40:40,778
things to him, Alby.

570
00:40:41,692 --> 00:40:42,700
Things that...

571
00:40:43,727 --> 00:40:47,061
no man should bear,
or bear witness to.

572
00:40:48,193 --> 00:40:49,193
He never broke.

573
00:40:50,142 --> 00:40:51,263
Not once

574
00:40:51,659 --> 00:40:57,169
did he waver
in his undying loyalty to his country.

575
00:40:58,158 --> 00:41:00,758
Well, it was my hope
that by taking a piece...

576
00:41:00,956 --> 00:41:04,704
just a piece of this great man with me,

577
00:41:05,213 --> 00:41:07,200
that maybe I, too, could,

578
00:41:07,615 --> 00:41:12,494
you know, one day achieve that kind
of courage, or that kind of honor.

579
00:41:14,624 --> 00:41:15,631
Yeah.

580
00:41:16,446 --> 00:41:17,930
I want you to put this away.

581
00:41:19,005 --> 00:41:20,005
All right.

582
00:41:30,887 --> 00:41:31,887
Look at me.

583
00:41:32,056 --> 00:41:33,600
- What?
- You're okay.

584
00:41:34,929 --> 00:41:35,965
You're okay.

585
00:41:37,057 --> 00:41:38,226
- All right?
- Yeah.

586
00:41:38,601 --> 00:41:40,351
- I'm okay.
- All right.

587
00:41:40,728 --> 00:41:41,540
Yeah.

588
00:41:42,472 --> 00:41:43,980
You guys need to see this.

589
00:41:44,159 --> 00:41:45,166
Come on.

590
00:41:49,871 --> 00:41:51,331
You see?
You see that?

591
00:41:52,774 --> 00:41:55,511
I noticed it before, but
I didn't really pay it any attention.

592
00:41:55,632 --> 00:41:58,472
I thought it was some sniper laser,
but look at it.

593
00:41:58,934 --> 00:42:00,743
- It's morse.
- Yeah, that's right, Hank.

594
00:42:00,863 --> 00:42:02,825
That's morse,
and you see what it's saying?

595
00:42:02,945 --> 00:42:03,945
Pro patria.

596
00:42:04,070 --> 00:42:05,396
"For our country," man.

597
00:42:05,621 --> 00:42:08,042
That's our motto. It's 1013.
Deke is out there.

598
00:42:08,221 --> 00:42:10,331
Yes, he is, boys, that's right...
Yes, he is.

599
00:42:19,539 --> 00:42:20,726
Guys...

600
00:42:21,301 --> 00:42:22,413
I think I got it.

601
00:42:23,599 --> 00:42:25,602
I found a way to get our boys out.

